      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos from the james webb telescope and i cant stop thinking about how small everything is. like, even if i do something important or love someone or struggle to survive, it literally doesn't matter. the sun is gonna die, the universe is gonna go cold, and every single thing we've ever done will be erased. it feels like we're just playing a game that's already been lost. what's even the point of trying to keep going when the end result is just total nothingness?",
